text: (intriguing music)
- My name is Emily Johnson

and I'm a software
engineering manager at AWS.
I've been with AWS for two years
and I've been with Amazon for nine years.

The coolest thing I've achieved
is expanding the industry
for training in simulation.
So what that is...

When you are training
computer vision model models,

you need live data images
of something like stop signs

and street signs and
other things for a robot
but there's not enough data around
to properly train a model.

So synthetic images has become
a very cutting-edge area
that you can put into training data sets.
Autonomous systems have a very wide range,
if you even look at Amazon.

so Amazon has Computer
Vision in Amazon Go Stores

and those are what we
call like non interactive.
So then humans don't really interact
with that type of system.

But even at Amazon, we also
have robotics in our warehouses
which is probably the biggest use case
for robotics at Amazon.
My goal for autonomous systems
is to build out and make the public feel
like they can trust Amazon,

as well as just autonomous
vehicles in general.
(upbeat music)
